aders_seat1      = [[Bonaventure (provincial electoral district)|Bonaventure]]\n| last_election1     = 33 seats, 39.54%\n| seats1             = 43\n| seat_change1       = {{increase}}10\n| popular_vote1      = 70,345\n| percentage1        = 44.54%\n| swing1             = {{increase}}5.0[[Percentage point|pp]]\n\n| image2             = Louis-Olivier Taillon.jpg\n| image2_size        = 150x150px\n| colour2            = {{Canadian party colour|QC|UN|nohash}}\n| leader2            = [[Louis-Olivier Taillon]]\n| leader_since2      = 1887\n| party2             = {{Canadian party colour|QC|UN|name}}\n| leaders_seat2      = [[Montcalm (provincial electoral district)|Montcalm]] ''(lost re-election)''\n| last_election2     = 26 seats, 46.19%\n| seats2             = 23\n| seat_change2       = {{decrease}}3\n| popular_vote2      = 71,695\n| percentage2        = 45.39%\n| swing2             = {{decrease}}0.8[[Percentage point|pp]]\n\n| map_image          =\n| map_size           =\n| map_caption        =\n| title              = Premier\n| before_election    = [[Honor\u00e9 Mercier]]\n| before_party       = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|name}}\n| after_election     = [[Honor\u00e9 Mercier]]\n| posttitle          = Premier after election\n| after_party        = {{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|name}}\n}}\nThe '''1890 Quebec general election''' was held on June 17, 1890 to elect members of the [[7th Legislative Assembly of Quebec|7th Legislative Assembly]] of the Province of [[Quebec]], Canada.  The incumbent [[Quebec Liberal Party]] [[Parti national]] coalition led by [[Honor\u00e9 Mercier]], was re-elected, defeating the [[Conservative Party of Quebec (historical)|Quebec Conservative Party]], led by [[Louis-Olivier Taillon]].\n\nA scandal and charges of corruption cut short Mercier's term of office.  He was later cleared of all charges, but his political career was ended.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.biographi.ca/en/bio/mercier_honore_12E.html|title=Biography \u2013 MERCIER, HONOR\u00c9 \u2013 Volume XII (1891-1900)|last=Dufour|first=Pierre|date=1998|work=Dictionary of Canadian Biography|access-date=2018-11-12|last2=Hamelin|first2=Jean}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse border-color: #444444\"\n|- bgcolor=\"darkgray\"\n!rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"|Party\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Party Leader\n!rowspan=\"2\"|# of<br />candidates\n!colspan=\"3\"|Seats\n!colspan=\"3\"|Popular Vote\n|- bgcolor=\"darkgray\"\n|align=\"center\"|[[1886 Quebec general election|1886]]\n|align=\"center\"|'''Elected'''\n|align=\"center\"|% Change\n|align=\"center\"|#\n|align=\"center\"|%\n|align=\"center\"|% Change\n{{Canadian party colour|QC|Liberal|row-name}} \n| [[Honor\u00e9 Mercier]] <!--leader-->\n|align=\"right\"|&nbsp;  <!--cand-->\n|align=\"right\"|33   <!--prev-->\n!align=\"right\"|43    <!--elected-->\n|align=\"right\"|+30.3%  <!--%ch.seats-->\n|align=\"right\"|70,345   <!--vote-->\n|align=\"right\"| 44.54%   <!--%vote-->\n|align=\"right\"|+5.0%   <!--%ch.votes-->\n{{Canadian party colour|QC|Conservative (historical)|row-name}}  \n| [[Louis-Olivier Taillon]]   <!--leader-->\n|align=\"right\"|&nbsp;   <!--cand-->\n|align=\"right\"| 26  <!--prev-->\n!align=\"right\"| 23  <!--elected-->\n|align=\"right\"| -11.5%   <!--%ch.seats-->\n|align=\"right\"|71,695   <!--vote-->\n|align=\"right\"| 45.39%   <!--%vote-->\n|align=\"right\"| -0.8%   <!--%ch.votes-->\n{{Canadian_politics/party_colours/Independents/row}}\n|colspan=2|Independent Conservative\n|align=\"right\"|&nbsp;  <!--cand-->\n|align=\"right\"|3   <!--prev-->\n!align=\"right\"|1   <!--elected-->\n|align=\"right\"|-66.7%   <!--%ch.seats-->\n|rowspan=4 align=\"right\"|15,888      <!--vote-->\n|rowspan=4 align=\"right\"| 10.06%    <!--%vote-->\n|rowspan=4 align=\"right\"|-3.6%   <!--%ch.votes-->\n{{Canadian_politics/party_colours/Independents/row}}\n|''[[Parti national]]''\n| &nbsp;              <!--leader-->\n|align=\"right\"|&nbsp;  <!